{"word":"H4325 - מַיִם - mayim - mah'-yim - Piss","slug":"H4325","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">מַיִם</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>mayim"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>mah'-yim"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Piss"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DE;&#x05D9;&#x05DD; - mayim</b> - <i>mah'-yim</i><p/>Dual of a primitive noun (but used in a singular sense); <i>water</i>; figuratively <i>juice</i>; by euphemism <i>urine</i>, <i>semen: - </i> + piss, wasting, water (-ing, [-course, -flood, -spring])."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4313\">H4313</a>, <a href=\"#/H4314\">H4314</a>"}]}